nning things were really simple    this is the beatles documentary against which all other beatles documentaries must be measured  a film about the beatle who changed the most and who was  for decades  the least understood  the director   martin scorsese  uses conventional documentary techniques   concert footage  interviews and archival treasures that include home movies  but he develops his portrait over the course of     minutes  at the end of which you may feel that you hardly knew george harrison at all  write to joe morgenstern at joe morgenstern wsj com 
